venue.name: The Pancake Manor

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

venue.description: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, Booze. Serving food 24 hours a day, 364 days a year.

items.text: If you're a chocoholic make sure you give the Chocolate Jewels or Blackforest a try.
You must try maple syrup and hot chips
Be careful when you order, the portions may not look much but even a short stack of 2 pancakes is enough to fill you up!
Crawl here whilst drunk with a #btub entourage.
Omg pancakes the size of dinner plates and thicker than mother in laws thighs. Get one plate and share!
You must always flirt with the staff! Even if its 3am in the morning.
Get the bananarama!
Open 24 hours! Perfect for that late night pancake craving.
Eating pancake in a former church?! How cool is that ;)
Make sure you let them know when you make a big booking that you want to sit together or you might get a lecture for expecting otherwise!
if u wanna to sitting hours and dine i guess it's the best place..and its open 24 hours
Dinner set menu: Mexican crepe and Macadamia madness.
You'll want to eat absolutely everything on the menu and you'll be sad that you can't!
Oh look, fatties unite.
The round table is ours stay out
Must try the chocolate jewels
Open 24 hours, they serve both sweet AND savory pancakes and crepes. They alsi have steak in the menu if you don't feel like having breakfast food.
Very delicious packages at a place that is open for the entire day and built in what used to be an old church.  Get the ice cream of top of the pancakes, it will be worth it.
Double pancake is just enough to fill you up, the taste is OK. The place is packed at lunch time, and the service is VERY slow.
Lugar fantástico com opções de café da manhã americano(salsichas, bacon, ovos, panquecas). Tem varias opções de panquecas, todas deliciosas, além do fato de estar em uma igreja antiga.
